span%3E%3Cspan%3EAround%20this%20time%2C%20we%20were%20exposed%20to%20the%20activities%20of%20a%20cultural%20group%20called%20the%20Jana%20Natya%20Mandali.%20It%20relentlessly%20propagated%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20struggles%20against%20oppression%20in%20rural%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20chief%20architect%20of%20that%20mandali%20was%20a%20short%2C%20well-built%2C%20plucky%20man%20with%20a%20beard%20and%20a%20stick%20in%20his%20hand%2C%20always%20wearing%20a%20dhoti%20like%20Mahatma%20Gandhi.%20His%20name%20was%20Gaddar%2C%20a%20radical%20folk%20singer%20and%20balladeer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGaddar%20was%20an%20engineering%20student%20in%20Osmania%20University%20who%20gave%20up%20his%20studies%20while%20some%20of%20his%20classmates%20went%20on%20to%20become%20experts%20in%20different%20fields%20of%20engineering.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20had%20an%20opportunity%20to%20meet%20one%20of%20Gaddar%E2%80%99s%20close%20friends%20and%20classmate%20%E2%80%93%20then%20a%20professor%20of%20aeronautical%20engineering%20in%20Washington%20University%2C%20Seattle%20%E2%80%93%20in%201999.%20I%20was%20there%20to%20cover%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organization%E2%80%99s%20Seattle%20Ministerial%20Meeting.%20That%20meeting%20collapsed%20like%20a%20pack%20of%20cards%20in%20the%20face%20of%20fierce%20and%20violent%20anti-globalisation%20protests.%20A%20day%20after%20the%20meeting%2C%20I%20stayed%20in%20the%20professor%E2%80%99s%20home%20discussing%20Gaddar.%20I%20vividly%20remember%20what%20that%20the%20professor%20said%20%E2%80%93%20he%20felt%20sad%20when%20he%20thought%20of%20Gaddar%20because%20he%20was%20a%20fine%20student%20and%20could%20have%20been%20teaching%20in%20any%20of%20the%20best%20universities%20today.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20Gaddar%2C%20dedicated%20his%20life%20to%20the%20cause%20of%20awakening%20the%20rural%20poor%20through%20his%20powerful%20folk