5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGPT-4%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20other%20powerful%20models%20cleverly%20answer%20questions%20immediately%2C%20so%20there's%20less%20need%20to%20send%20users%20to%20the%20sources%20of%20the%20original%20information.%20This%20may%20be%20a%20great%20user%20experience%2C%20but%20the%20incentives%20to%20share%20high-quality%20free%20information%20online%20begin%20to%20break%20down%20pretty%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20would%20any%20producer%20of%20free%20online%20content%20let%20OpenAI%20scrape%20its%20material%20when%20that%20data%20will%20be%20used%20to%20train%20future%20LLMs%20that%20later%20compete%20with%20that%20creator%20by%20pulling%20users%20away%20from%20their%20site%3F%20You%20can%20already%20see%20this%20in%20action%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstack-overflow-crisis-future-of-online-data-ai-world-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efewer%20people%20visit%20Stack%20Overflow%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20software%20coding%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESelf-sabotage%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20self-sabotage%20to%20let%20OpenAI's%20GPTbot%20crawl%20your%20website.%20This%20realization%20is%20spreading%20pretty%20swiftly%20among%20online%20communities.%20The%20Verge%2C%20a%20digital%20publication%20that%20competes%20with%20Insider%2C%20looks%20like%20it%20took%20steps%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FGoran_Majic%2Fstatus%2F1688664959801008129%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblock%20GPTbot%20already%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20how%20long%20OpenAI's%20spiderbot%20has%20been%20lurking%20around%20online.%20The%20company%20recently%20announced%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.openai.com%2Fdocs%2Fgptbot%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eway%20to%20block%20GPTbot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20using%20a%20common%20protocol%20called%20robots.txt.%20Some%20creators%20have%20already%20implemented%20this%2C%20although%20some%20wonder%20whether%20OpenAI%20already%20had%20a%20bot%20secretly%20scooping%20up%20everyone's%20online%20data%20for%20months%20or%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFinally%2C%20after%20soaking%20up%20all%20your%20copyrighted%20content%20to%20build%20their%20proprietary%20product%2C%20OpenAI%20gives%20you%20a%20way%20to%20prevent%20your%20content%20from%20being%20used%20to%20further%20improve%20their%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20Prasad%20Dhumal%2C%20a%20search%20engine%20optimization%20consultant%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fprasaddhumal_%2Fstatus%2F1688517769158160384%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20on%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20now%20blocking%20another%20one%20of%20OpenAI's%20scraping%20bots.%20You%20can%20too.%20(I%20don't%20know%20if%20this%20is%20the%20secret%20one%20we%20couldn't%20block%20before%20or%20if%20that%20one%20is%20still%20in%20use.)%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fclarkesworld%2Fstatus%2F1688600561447268370%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20Neil%20Clarke%2C%20editor%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclarkesworldmagazine.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClarkesworld%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20science%20fiction%20and%20fantasy%20magazine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETrust%20is%20evaporating%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20Clarke%20about%20his%20decision%2C%20and%20his%20responses%20reveal%20how%20quickly%20trust%20has%20evaporated%20between%20online%20content%20creators%20and%20AI%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOpenAI%20and%20other%20'AI'%20creators%20have%20demonstrated%20repeatedly%20that%20they%20have%20no%20respect%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20authors%2C%20artists%2C%20and%20other%20creative%20professionals.%20Their%20products%20are%20largely%20based%20on%20the%20copyrighted%20works%20of%20others%2C%20taken%20without%20authorization%20or%20compensation%2C%26quot%3B%20Clarke%20wrote%20in%20an%20email.%20%26quot%3BThey%20repeatedly%20defend%20the%20use%20of%20these%20practices%20and%20have%20only%20recently%20identified%20this%20bot.%20It's%20not%20entirely%20clear%20that%20opting%20out%20of%20this%20bot%20(and%20CCBot)%20will%20be%20sufficient%20to%20avoid%20having%20content%20harvested%20by%20OpenAI.%20Their%20track%20record%20on%20transparency%20leaves%20much%20to%20be%20desired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECCBot%20is%20another%20digital%20spider%20that%20crawls%20the%20web%20collecting%20all%20the%20content.%20This%20is%20run%20by%20an%20organization%20called%20Common%20Crawl%2C%20which%20is%20a%20major%20supplier%20of%20training%20data%20for%20AI%20models.%20Common%20Crawl%20stores%20all%20this%20information%20regularly%2C%20so%20even%20if%20you%20block%20its%20bot%20now%2C%20your%20data%20has%20already%20probably%20been%20taken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20unaware%20of%20anyone%20that%20has%20managed%20to%20get%20Common%20Crawl%20to%20remove%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20Clarke%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20tried%2C%20but%20have%20had%20no%20response.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Opt-in'%20not%20'opt-out'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EClarke%20and%20others%20are%20now%20calling%20for%20these%20AI%20spiderbots%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bopt-in%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20%26quot%3Bopt-out.%26quot%3B%20Right%20now%2C%20OpenAI%20scrapes%20everyone's%20data%20as%20the%20default%2C%20and%20creators%20must%20take%20steps%20to%20opt%20out%20and%20actively%20block%20it.%20An%20%26quot%3Bopt-in%26quot%3B%20approach%20would%20require%20OpenAI%20to%20ask%20permission%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BData%20collection%20methods%20for%20these%20models%20must%20become%20strictly%20opt-in.%20Many%20people%20will%20not%20find%20out%20how%20to%20protect%20their%20work%20until%20it%20has%20already%20been%20taken%2C%20yet%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Clarke%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BSince%20we%20are%20presently%20unable%20to%20have%20our%20content%20removed%20from%20existing%20models%20and%20scraped%20data%20sets%2C%20opt-out%20is%20not%20enough.%20It%20is%20not%20our%20responsibility%20to%20provide%20data%20for%20these%20companies%2C%20nor%20should%20they%20be%20allowed%20to%20simply%20take%20it%20without%20consent%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20benefits%20they%20imagine%20coming%20from%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20OpenAI%20about%20all%20this%20on%20Tuesday%20morning.%20The%20company%20didn't%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPaying%20for%20AI%20training%20data%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20has%20made%20an%20effort%20to%20respect%20some%20online%20data.%20GPTbot%20is%20now%20designed%20to%20filter%20out%20sources%20that%20require%20paywall%20access%20and%20to%20remove%20other%20sources%20known%20to%20gather%20personally%20identifiable%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20recently%20announced%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fopenai-chatgpt-associated-press-ap-f86f84c5bcc2f3b98074b38521f5f75a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edeal%20with%20the%20Associated%20Press%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20OpenAI%20will%20pay%20to%20license%20AP%20content%20for%20AI%20training%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20company%20paid%20for%20this%20data%2C%20why%20doesn't%20it%20also%20pay%20for%20everyone%20else's%20information%2C%20too%3F%20I%20asked%20the%20company%20and%20it%20didn't%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Block%20it'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20hasn't%20contacted%20Neil%20Clarke%20at%