ary%20Bars%20Use%20of%20Chinese%20Components%20in%20Drone%20Manufacture%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F08181023%2FMQ-9B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Citing%20security%20concerns%2C%20the%20Indian%20military%20has%20barred%20the%20use%20of%20Chinese%20equipment%20and%20components%20in%20surveillance%20drones%20that%20are%20manufactured%20domestically%2C%20news%20agency%20Reuters%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Findia-bars-makers-military-drones-using-chinese-parts-2023-08-08%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20meeting%20minutes%20reviewed%20by%20Reuters%2C%20the%20military%20told%20potential%20bidders%20that%20parts%20made%20in%20%E2%80%9Ccountries%20sharing%20land%20borders%20with%20India%20will%20not%20be%20acceptable%20for%20security%20reasons%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20military%20tender%20document%20also%20said%20that%20such%20parts%20contained%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20loopholes%E2%80%9D%20that%20could%20put%20crucial%20Indian%20military%20data%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20unnamed%20senior%20defence%20official%20told%20the%20news%20agency%20that%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Ccountries%20sharing%20land%20borders%E2%80%9D%20was%20actually%20a%20reference%20to%20China%2C%20reflecting%20concerns%20around%20allegations%20that%20it%20has%20been%20involved%20in%20cyberattacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20immediate%20consequence%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%E2%80%99s%20decision%20is%20that%20domestic%20drone%20manufacture%20will%20become%20costlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20today%20I%20buy%20equipment%20from%20China%20but%20I%20say%20I%20want%20to%20make%20it%20in%20India%2C%20the%20cost%20will%20go%20up%2050%25%20%E2%80%A6%20We%20as%20a%20nation%20need%20to%20be%20ready%20to%20help%20the%20ecosystem%20build%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20Reuters%20quoted%20the