.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAny%20recourse%20to%20public%20opinion%20has%20to%20be%20sought%20through%20established%20institutions.%20You%20cannot%20envisage%20a%20Brexit-type%20referendum%E2%80%A6%20That%20was%20a%20political%20decision%20taken%20by%20the%20then%20government%20in%20the%20U.K%E2%80%A6%20But%20within%20a%20constitution%20like%20ours%2C%20there%20is%20no%20question%20of%20a%20referendum%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Farticle-370-hearing-india-seeks-public-opinion-through-established-institutions-not-brexit-type-referendums-says-cji%2Farticle67172076.ece%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppearing%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20petitioners%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%20had%20accused%20the%20Union%20government%20of%20reading%20down%20the%20Article%20%E2%80%9Cunilaterally%E2%80%9D%20without%20making%20an%20effort%20to%20understand%20the%20will%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20want%20to%20sever%20such%20a%20special%20relationship%20with%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20you%20had%20to%20ultimately%20seek%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20people.%20The%20will%20of%20the%20people%20was%20central%20to%20this%20decision.%20It%20should%20have%20been%20a%20political%20decision%E2%80%A6%20What%20happened%20in%20Brexit%3F%20There%20was%20no%20constitutional%20provision%20for%20a%20referendum.%20Yet%2C%20they%20asked%20for%20public%20opinion%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20had%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20the%20Article%20was%20abrogated%20through%20a%20series%20of%20%E2%80%9Cexecutive%20acts%E2%80%9D%2C%20beginning%20with%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Legislative%20Assembly%20and%20the%20state%20government.%20Subsequently%2C%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20imposed%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20and%20a%20proviso%20to%20Article%20370%20(3)%20was%20tweaked%20to%20%E2%80%9Csidestep%20the%20pre-condition%20of%20getting%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20now%20defunct%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Constituent%20Assembly%20before%20declaring%20Article%20370%20inoperative%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported%20Sibal%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20%5BIndian%20government%5D%20played%20a%20fraud%20on%20the%20constitution%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20declared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20asserting%20that%20such%20a%20move%20required%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20state%20and%20its%20people%2C%20Sibal%20argued%20that%20the%20relationship%20between%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20was%20%E2%80%9Cpurely%20federal%E2%80%9D%20and%20not%20%E2%80%9Cquasi-federal%E2%80%9D%20like%20the%20other%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20courtroom%20exchange%2C%20the%20CJI%20also%20asked%20the%20petitioners%20how%20it%20could%20be%20assumed%20that%20Article%20370%20had%20assumed%20a%20permanent%20character%20in%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWas%20a%20constitutional%20amendment%2C%20required%20in%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20to%20drop%20the%20%E2%80%98temporary%E2%80%99%20nature%20of%20370%20and%20make%20it%20permanent%20or%20can%20it%20be%20deemed%20permanent%20merely%20on%20the%20basis%20that%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Constituent%20Assembly%20did%20not%20abrogate%20it%20before%20dissolving%20in%201957%3F%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691508910000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F15192226%2F2022_11img14_Nov_2022_PTI11_14_2022_000175B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-chandrachud-says-brexit-like-referendum-not-possible%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20petitioners%20argued%20that%20Article%20370%20was%20read%20down%20through%20a%20series%20of%20'executive%20acts'%20without%20conside