ad%20of%20misinformation%20and%20hate%20speech%20through%20news%20channels%20and%20social%20media%E2%80%9D%2C%20warning%20that%20%E2%80%9Crapidly%20increasing%20levels%20of%20radicalization%E2%80%9D%20are%20%E2%80%9Cfermenting%20an%20atmosphere%20conducive%20to%20large-scale%20violence%20%E2%80%9C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20written%20in%20their%20personal%20capacity%2C%20the%20faculty%20members%20said%20they%20wanted%20to%20draw%20Corporate%20India%E2%80%99s%C2%A0attention%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfragile%20state%20of%20internal%20security%20with%20an%20increasing%20risk%20of%20violent%20conflicts%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%20They%20said%20that%20over%C2%A0the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20%E2%80%9Can%20open%20and%20public%20exhibit%20of%20hatred%20towards%20minorities%20in%20public%20discourse%20has%20become%20common%20practice%E2%80%9D%20in%20political%20discourse%2C%20television%20news%20and%20social%20media%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20trends%20concern%20corporate%20India%2C%20%E2%80%9Cas%20they%20point%20towards%20an%20increasing%20risk%20of%20violent%20conflicts%20in%20the%20country.%20In%20the%20worst%20case%2C%20such%20acts%20of%20violence%20could%20culminate%20into%20a%20genocide%2C%20which%20would%20annihilate%20the%20social%20fabric%20as%20well%20as%20the%20economy%20of%20the%20country%2C%20casting%20a%20long%20dark%20shadow%20over%20India%E2%80%99s%20future.%20Corporate%20India%2C%20which%20hopes%20to%20reach%20new%20frontiers%20of%20international%20growth%20and%20innovation%20in%20the%2021st%20century%2C%20cannot%20afford%20to%20live%20with%20even%20a%20small%20possibility%20of%20such%20a%20scenario%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20letter%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20signatories%20said%20that%20because%20India%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20tolerance%20and%20peaceful%20coexistence%20of%20different%20faiths%2C%20they%20would%20like%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20risk%20of%20large-scale%20violent%20conflicts%20or%20genocide%20in%20India%20is%20still%20s