20particular%20community%20are%20being%20brought%20down%20%E2%80%9Cunder%20the%20guise%20of%20law%20and%20order%20problem%2C%20and%20an%20exercise%20of%20ethnic%20cleansing%20is%20being%20conducted%20by%20the%20state%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691491212000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08154007%2Fimage2.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fnuh-demolitions-residents-due-process-damages%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22People%20whose%20houses%20and%20establishments%20were%20demolished%20say%20only%20properties%20of%20Muslims%20were%20singled%20out%20by%20the%20administration%2C%20a%20question%20that%20even%20the%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20high%20court%20raised%20while%20halting%20the%20action.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fnuh-demolitions-residents-due-process-damages%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Imran%20Khan%20wants%20a%20transfer%20from%20his%20%E2%80%98tiny%2C%20dirty%E2%80%99%20jail%20cell%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691490115000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102533676%2Cimgsize-25316.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fimran-khan-wants-a-transfer-from-his-tiny-dirty-jail-cell%2Farticleshow%2F102533664.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102533664.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EPakistani%20ex-Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Khan%20has%20launched%20a%20legal%20bid%20to%20be%20moved%20from%20a%20%26quot%3Btiny%2C%20dirty%26quot%3B%20cell%20to%20an%20upgraded%20facility%20which%20offers%20air-cooling%20and%20better%20food%2C%20following%20his%20conviction%20in%20a%20corruption%20case.%20Khan%20was%20sentenced%20to%20three%20years%20in%20jail%20last%20week%20after%20being%20found%20guilty%20of%20hiding%20earnings%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20state%20gifts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fimran-khan-wants-a-transfer-from-his-tiny-dirty-jail-cell%2Farticleshow%2F102533664.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fimran-khan-wants-a-transfer-from-his-tiny-dirty-jail-cell%2Famp_articleshow%2F102533664.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fimran-khan-wants-a-transfer-from-his-tiny-dirty-jail-cell%2Famp_articleshow%2F102533664.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Quit%20India'%3A%20The%20Last%20Nail%20in%20the%20Coffin%20of%20the%20British%20Empire%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F08%2FQuit-India-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EJapan%20bombed%20Pearl%20Harbour%2C%20an%20American%20base%2C%20in%20December%201941%2C%20and%20this%20drew%20the%20US%20into%20the%20Second%20World%20War.%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20armies%20began%20to%20march%20swiftly%20through%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20bringing%20the%20war%20to%20the%20very%20doors%20of%20India.%20If%20the%20Japanese%20had%20to%20be%20resisted%2C%20something%20had%20to%20be%20done%20to%20involve%20the%20Indians%20in%20the%20war%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERealising%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20situation%2C%20Winston%20Churchill%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20Britain%2C%20under%20pressure%20from%20American%20President%20Roosevelt%2C%20agreed%2C%20reluctantly%2C%20to%20consider%20proposal%20for%20a%20self-government%20in%20India.%20Sir%20Stafford%20Cripps%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20War%20Cabinet%2C%20was%20dispatched%20to%20India%20with%20the%20proposals%20of%20the%20British%20government.%20He%20met%20the%20Congress%20president%20Maulana%20Azad%20on%20March%2025%2C%201942%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20meeting%20with%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru.%20They%20both%20told%20him%20that%20the%20viceroy%20should%20only%20be%20a%20constitutional%20head%2C%20and%20the%20proposed%20Council%20should%20have%20an%20Indian%20as%20defence%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20was%20rejected%20by%20the%20War%20Cabinet%20when%20the%20demand%20was%20placed%20before%20Churchill%20by%20Cripps%20on%20March%2027.%20Cripps%20met%20M.K.%20Gandhi%20and%20showed%20him%20the%20proposal%2C%20to%20which%20the%20latter%20stated%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20did%20you%20come%20if%20this%20is%20what%20you%20have%20to%20offer%20%E2%80%93%20I%20would%20advise%20you%20to%20take%20the%20next%20plane%20home.%E2%80%9D%20Gandhi%20was%20also%20believed%20to%20have%20remarked%20that%20Cripps%E2%80%99%20proposals%20were%20%E2%80%9Ca%20post%20dated%20cheque%20on%20a%20crashing%20bank%E2%80%9D.%20But%20this%20statement%20attributed%20to%20Gandhi%20in%20Sewagram%20was%20denied%20by%20him%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctissue%20of%20lies%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20expected%20failure%20of%20the%20Cripps%20Mission%20showed%20that%20Britain%20was%20not%20willing%20to%20make%20any%20political%20concessions%20during%20the%20war.%20But%20then%20could%20Britain%20defend%20India%3F%20Singapore%2C%20a%20heavily%20guarded%20fortress%20of%20Britain%2C%20had%20fallen%20on%20February%2015%2C%201942%20and%20then%20Rangoon%20on%20March%207.%20The%20war%20was%20now%20on%20the%20borders%20of%20India.%20The%20country%20was%20seething%20with%20frustration.%20It%20wanted%20action.%20That%20was%20also%20the%20thinking%20of%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20(CWC)%20decided%20to%20meet%20in%20April%201942.%20Gandhi%20sent%20a%20draft%20for%20the%20CWC%20meeting%20through%20Miraben%2C%20saying%20Britain%20could%20not%20defend%20India%2C%20that%20India%20had%20no%20quarrel%20with%20any%20power%20including%20the%20Japanese%2C%20and%20that%20British%20and%20all%20foreign%20troops%20should%20be%20immediately%20withdraw%20from%20India.%C2%A0%20Gandhi%20was%20prepared%20to%20leave%20the%20Congress%20with%20his%20followers%20if%20his%20draft%20was%20not%20accepted%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20time%20has%20come%20when%20every%20one%20of%20us%20has%20to%20choose%20his%20own%20course.%E2%80%9D%20Though%20there%20was%20a%20majority%20of%2011%20to%206%20in%20the%20Working%20Committee%20in%20favour%20of%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20draft%2C%20to%20avoid%20a%20split%2C%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20alternative%20and%20less%20militant%20draft%20was%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20showdown%20between%20Gandhi%20and%20some%20of%20his%20lieutenants%20on%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20and%20Nehru%20and%20Azad%20on%20the%20other%2C%20in%20the%20next%20meeting%20of%20the%20Working%20Committee%20meeting%20which%20began%20on%20July%205%2C%201942%20at%20Wardha%20and%20lasted%20for%20several%20days.%20Azad%20felt%20that%20if%20Japan%20invaded%20India%20she%20should%20be%20resisted%2C%20for%20it%20would%20be%20most%20undesirable%20to%20change%20an%20old%20master%20which%2C%20in%20the%20course%20of%20time%2C%20had%20%E2%80%9Cbecome%20effete%20and%20was%20losing%20its%20grip%20for%20a%20new%20and%20virile%20conqueror%E2%80%9D.%20So%20he%20opposed%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20plan%20of%20civil%20disobedience.%20Nehru%20supported%20him.%20However%2C%20a%20compromised%20was%20reached.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2014%2C%20the%20CWC%20passed%20a%20resolution%20calling%20upon%20the%20British%20to%20quit%20India%3B%20but%20adding%2C%20at%20the%20insistence%20of%20Nehru%2C%20that%20after%20such%20withdrawal%20the%20Congress%20was%20agreeable%20to%20the%20stationing%20of%20the%20armed%20forces%20of%20Allied%20Powers%20to%20resist%20the%20Japanese%20aggression.%20The%20die%20was%20thus%20cast%20and%20there%20was%20now%20no%20going%20back.%20It%20was%20also%20decided%20to%20call%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20AICC%20in%20Bombay%20on%20August%207%20to%20ratify%20the%20resolution.%20The%20Bombay%20meeting%20of%20the%20AICC%20confirmed%20the%20Wardha%20CWC%20resolution.%20On%20August%208%2C%20Nehru%20moved%20the%20%E2%80%98Quit%20India%E2%80%99%20resolution%20and%20Sardar%20Patel%20seconded%20it.%C2%A0%20The%20resolution%20was%20passed%20amidst%20scenes%20of%20great%20enthusiasm%20and%20nationalist%20fervour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20Quit%20India%20movement%20was%20launched%2C%20Gandhi%20was%20asked%20whether%20he%20would%20call%20off%20the%20movement%20as%20he%20did%20in%201922%20in%20the%20event%20of%20any%20eruption%20of%20violence.%20He%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20the%20same%20Gandhi%20as%20I%20was%20in%201922%2C%20I%20attach%20the%20same%20importance%20to%20non-violence%20that%20I%20did%20then.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20he%20was%20not%20the%20same%20Gandhi.%20According%20to%20historian%20Sankar%20Ghose%2C%20%E2%80%9CHe%2C%20in%20his%20seventies%2C%20was%20an%20impatient%20Gandhi%20who%20could%20not%20wait%20for%20Independence%2C%20whatever%20the%20consequences.%20So%20he%20gave%20the%20call%2C%20%E2%80%98Do%20or%20Die.%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98I%20waited%20and%20waited%2C%E2%80%99%20Gandhi%20wrote%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EHarijan%20%3C%2Fem%3Eon%20June%207%2C%201942%2C%20%E2%80%98until%20the%20country%20should%20develop%20non-violent%20strength%20necessary%20to%20throw%20off%20the%20foreign%20yoke.%20I%20feel%20that%20I%20cannot%20afford%20to%20wait%20%E2%80%A6If%20in%20spite%20of%20all%20precautions%20rioting%20takes%20place%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20helped.%E2%80%99%20He%20now%20said%20that%20everyone%20was%20%E2%80%98free%20to%20go%20to%20the%20fullest%20length%E2%80%99%2C%20though%20only%20under%20%3Cem%3Eahimsa%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20%E2%80%98the%20fullest%20length%E2%80%99%20could%20include%20a%20general%20strike%20if%20that%20became%20a%20dire%20necessity.%20He%20was%20even%20prepared%20to%20tolerate%20%E2%80%98fifteen%20days%20of%20chaos%E2%80%99.%20He%20was%20no%20longer%20unduly%20perturbed%20by%20violence%20taking%20place.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%205%20in%20the%20morning%20of%20August%209%2C%20a%20day%20after%20the%20AICC%20ratified%20the%20Quit%20India%20resolution%2C%20Gandhi%2C%20Nehru%2C%20Patel%2C%20Azad%20and%20all%20top%20Congress%20leaders%20were%20arrested.%20Though%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20had%20been%20imprisoned%20at%20Aga%20Khan%20Palace%20at%20Poona%2C%20was%20released%20earlier%20in%20May%201944%20on%20grounds%20of%20health%2C%20Nehru%20was%20in%20prison%20at%20Ahmednagar%20Fort%20for%2034%20months%2C%20his%20longest%20ever%2C%20from%20August%201942%20to%20June%201945.%20The%20wholesale%20arrest%20of%20the%20leaders%20touched%20off%20a%20spontaneous%20popular%20revolt%20throughout%20India.%20For%20a%20week%20all%20business%20was%20paralysed%20in%20Bombay%2C%20Ahmedabad%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Bangalore%2C%20Calcutta%20and%20many%20other%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authorities%20let%20loose%20cruel%20repression.%20In%20Delhi%2C%20the%20police%20fired%20on%2047%20separate%20occasions%20on%20August%2011%20and%2012.%20In%20UP%20there%20were%2029%20firings%20between%20August%209%20and%2021%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20death%20of%2076%20persons%20and%20severe%20injury%20to%20114.%20In%20the%20Central%20Provinces%20the%20police%20killed%2064%2C%20wounded%20102%20and%20arrested%2011%2C088%20in%20the%20first%20three%20weeks.%20In%20Mysore%20State%20about%20600%20persons%20were%20killed%20by%20police%20firing%20during%20the%20first%20few%20days%20of%20the%20movement.%20In%20Patiala%2C%20eight%20students%20were%20killed%20while%20trying%20to%20hoist%20the%20national%20flag%20over%20a%20public%20building.%20Over%20100%20were%20shot%20in%20a%20Mysore%20procession.%20In%20Calcutta%20there%20were%20numerous%20firings%2C%20resulting%20in%20many%20deaths.%20The%20same%20was%20the%20case%20in%20all%20big%20cities.%20In%20Midnapore%20(Bengal)%20and%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20parallel%20governments%20were%20set%20up%20which%20functioned%20effectively%20for%20a%20short%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20casualties%20from%20August%209%20to%20November%2030%2C%201942%20were%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Secretary%20of%20State%20for%20India%2C%201%2C008%20killed%2C%20and%203%2C275%20seriously%20injured.%20The%20popular%20estimate%20was%20however%20very%20much%20higher.%20The%20number%20of%20people%20imprisoned%20was%20over%20100%2C000.%20The%20movement%20had%20taken%20a%20turn%20not%20contemplated%20by%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20Congress%20leaders.%20Infuriated%20by%20the%20wholesale%20arrest%20of%20their%20leaders%20and%20the%20cruel%20repression%20let%20loose%20by%20the%20authorities%2C%20people%20in%20several%20places%20destroyed%20public%20property%20like%20bridges%2C%20police%20stations%2C%20etc.%2C%20and%20removed%20even%20rail%20tracks%2C%20cut%20off%20telegraph%20wires%20and%20vented%20their%20anger%20in%20various%20other%20acts%20of%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcharya%20Kriplani%20(who%20was%20INC%20president%20in%201946-47)%20writes%20in%20his%20biography%20of%20Gandhi%3A%20%E2%80%9CHad%20the%20people%20had%20the%20guidance%20of%20the%20leaders%2C%20such%20wanton%20destruction%20would%20not%20have%20taken%20place.%20Even%20if%20Gandhiji%20alone%20were%20out%2C%20he%20would%20have%20undertaken%20a%20fast%20if%20nothing%20else%20had%20prevailed.%20It%20would%20have%20cooled%20down%20people%E2%80%99s%20ardour%20for%20destruction%20and%20the%20movement%20would%20have%20gone%20on%20generally%20on%20right%20lines.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Kriplani%20held%20the%20firm%20view%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20my%20opinion%20that%20India%20could%20not%20have%20achieved%20its%20independence%2C%20but%20for%20the%20accession%20of%20strength%20which%20the%20nation%20received%20by%20the%20successive%20struggles%20started%20by%20Gandhiji.%20A%20nation%20which%20could%20throw%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%20Empire%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20armies%20of%20all%20the%20Allies%20were%20on%20Indian%20soil%20could%20no%20more%20be%20held%20in%20thralldom.%E2%80%9D%20Even%20if%20one%20is%20wiser%20by%20hindsight%2C%20the%20Acharya%E2%80%99s%20opinion%20is%20difficult%20to%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPraveen%20Davar%20is%20former%20secretary%2C%20AICC%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EFreedom%20Struggle%20%26amp%3B%20Beyond%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691489452000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F08%2FQuit-India-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fquit-india-the-last-nail-in-the-coffin-of-the-british-empire%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20movement%20took%20a%20turn%20not%20contemplated%20by%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20Congress%20leaders.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fquit-india-the-last-nail-in-the-coffin-of-the-british-empire%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Quit%20India'%3A%20The%20Last%20Nail%20in%20the%20Coffin%20of%20the%20British%20Empire%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F08%2FQuit-India-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EJapan%20bombed%20Pearl%20Harbour%2C%20an%20American%20base%2C%20in%20December%201941%2C%20and%20this%20drew%20the%20US%20into%20the%20Second%20World%20War.%20Japan%E2%80%99s%20armies%20began%20to%20march%20swiftly%20through%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20bringing%20the%20war%20to%20the%20very%20doors%20of%20India.%20If%20the%20Japanese%20had%20to%20be%20resisted%2C%20something%20had%20to%20be%20done%20to%20involve%20the%20Indians%20in%20the%20war%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERealising%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20situation%2C%20Winston%20Churchill%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20Britain%2C%20under%20pressure%20from%20American%20President%20Roosevelt%2C%20agreed%2C%20reluctantly%2C%20to%20consider%20proposal%20for%20a%20self-government%20in%20India.%20Sir%20Stafford%20Cripps%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20War%20Cabinet%2C%20was%20dispatched%20to%20India%20with%20the%20proposals%20of%20the%20British%20government.%20He%20met%20the%20Congress%20president%20Maulana%20Azad%20on%20March%2025%2C%201942%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20meeting%20with%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru.%20They%20both%20told%20him%20that%20the%20viceroy%20should%20only%20be%20a%20constitutional%20head%2C%20and%20the%20proposed%20Council%20should%20have%20an%20Indian%20as%20defence%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20was%20rejected%20by%20the%20War%20Cabinet%20when%20the%20demand%20was%20placed%20before%20Churchill%20by%20Cripps%20on%20March%2027.%20Cripps%20met%20M.K.%20Gandhi%20and%20showed%20him%20the%20proposal%2C%20to%20which%20the%20latter%20stated%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20did%20you%20come%20if%20this%20is%20what%20you%20have%20to%20offer%20%E2%80%93%20I%20would%20advise%20you%20to%20take%20the%20next%20plane%20home.%E2%80%9D%20Gandhi%20was%20also%20believed%20to%20have%20remarked%20that%20Cripps%E2%80%99%20proposals%20were%20%E2%80%9Ca%20post%20dated%20cheque%20on%20a%20crashing%20bank%E2%80%9D.%20But%20this%20statement%20attributed%20to%20Gandhi%20in%20Sewagram%20was%20denied%20by%20him%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctissue%20of%20lies%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20expected%20failure%20of%20the%20Cripps%20Mission%20showed%20that%20Britain%20was%20not%20willing%20to%20make%20any%20political%20concessions%20during%20the%20war.%20But%20then%20could%20Britain%20defend%20India%3F%20Singapore%2C%20a%20heavily%20guarded%20fortress%20of%20Britain%2C%20had%20fallen%20on%20February%2015%2C%201942%20and%20then%20Rangoon%20on%20March%207.%20The%20war%20was%20now%20on%20the%20borders%20of%20India.%20The%20country%20was%20seething%20with%20frustration.%20It%20wanted%20action.%20That%20was%20also%20the%20thinking%20of%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20(CWC)%20decided%20to%20meet%20in%20April%201942.%20Gandhi%20sent%20a%20draft%20for%20the%20CWC%20meeting%20through%20Miraben%2C%20saying%20Britain%20could%20not%20defend%20India%2C%20that%20India%20had%20no%20quarrel%20with%20any%20power%20including%20the%20Japanese%2C%20and%20that%20British%20and%20all%20foreign%20troops%20should%20be%20immediately%20withdraw%20from%20India.%C2%A0%20Gandhi%20was%20prepared%20to%20leave%20the%20Congress%20with%20his%20followers%20if%20his%20draft%20was%20not%20accepted%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20time%20has%20come%20when%20every%20one%20of%20us%20has%20to%20choose%20his%20own%20course.%E2%80%9D%20Though%20there%20was%20a%20majority%20of%2011%20to%206%20in%20the%20Working%20Committee%20in%20favour%20of%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20draft%2C%20to%20avoid%20a%20split%2C%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20alternative%20and%20less%20militant%20draft%20was%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20showdown%20between%20Gandhi%20and%20some%20of%20his%20lieutenants%20on%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20and%20Nehru%20and%20Azad%20on%20the%20other%2C%20in%20the%20next%20meeting%20of%20the%20Working%20Committee%20meeting%20which%20began%20on%20July%205%2C%201942%20at%20Wardha%20and%20lasted%20for%20several%20days.%20Azad%20felt%20that%20if%20Japan%20invaded%20India%20she%20should%20be%20resisted%2C%20for%20it%20would%20be%20most%20undesirable%20to%20change%20an%20old%20master%20which%2C%20in%20the%20course%20of%20time%2C%20had%20%E2%80%9Cbecome%20effete%20and%20was%20losing%20its%20grip%20for%20a%20new%20and%20virile%20conqueror%E2%80%9D.%20So%20he%20opposed%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20plan%20of%20civil%20disobedience.%20Nehru%20supported%20him.%20However%2C%20a%20compromised%20was%20reached.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2014%2C%20the%20CWC%20passed%20a%20resolution%20calling%20upon%20the%20British%20to%20quit%20India%3B%20but%20adding%2C%20at%20the%20insistence%20of%20Nehru%2C%20that%20after%20such%20withdrawal%20the%20Congress%20was%20agreeable%20to%20the%20stationing%20of%20the%20armed%20forces%20of%20Allied%20Powers%20to%20resist%20the%20Japanese%20aggression.%20The%20die%20was%20thus%20cast%20and%20there%20was%20now%20no%20going%20back.%20It%20was%20also%20decided%20to%20call%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20AICC%20in%20Bombay%20on%20August%207%20to%20ratify%20the%20resolution.%20The%20Bombay%20meeting%20of%20the%20AICC%20confirmed%20the%20Wardha%20CWC%20resolution.%20On%20August%208%2C%20Nehru%20moved%20the%20%E2%80%98Quit%20India%E2%80%99%20resolution%20and%20Sardar%20Patel%20seconded%20it.%C2%A0%20The%20resolution%20was%20passed%20amidst%20scenes%20of%20great%20enthusiasm%20and%20nationalist%20fervour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20Quit%20India%20movement%20was%20launched%2C%20Gandhi%20was%20asked%20whether%20he%20would%20call%20off%20the%20movement%20as%20he%20did%20in%201922%20in%20the%20event%20of%20any%20eruption%20of%20violence.%20He%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20the%20same%20Gandhi%20as%20I%20was%20in%201922%2C%20I%20attach%20the%20same%20importance%20to%20non-violence%20that%20I%20did%20then.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20he%20was%20not%20the%20same%20Gandhi.%20According%20to%20historian%20Sankar%20Ghose%2C%20%E2%80%9CHe%2C%20in%20his%20seventies%2C%20was%20an%20impatient%20Gandhi%20who%20could%20not%20wait%20for%20Independence%2C%20whatever%20the%20consequences.%20So%20he%20gave%20the%20call%2C%20%E2%80%98Do%20or%20Die.%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98I%20waited%20and%20waited%2C%E2%80%99%20Gandhi%20wrote%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EHarijan%20%3C%2Fem%3Eon%20June%207%2C%201942%2C%20%E2%80%98until%20the%20country%20should%20develop%20non-violent%20strength%20necessary%20to%20throw%20off%20the%20foreign%20yoke.%20I%20feel%20that%20I%20cannot%20afford%20to%20wait%20%E2%80%A6If%20in%20spite%20of%20all%20precautions%20rioting%20takes%20place%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20helped.%E2%80%99%20He%20now%20said%20that%20everyone%20was%20%E2%80%98free%20to%20go%20to%20the%20fullest%20length%E2%80%99%2C%20though%20only%20under%20%3Cem%3Eahimsa%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20%E2%80%98the%20fullest%20length%E2%80%99%20could%20include%20a%20general%20strike%20if%20that%20became%20a%20dire%20necessity.%20He%20was%20even%20prepared%20to%20tolerate%20%E2%80%98fifteen%20days%20of%20chaos%E2%80%99.%20He%20was%20no%20longer%20unduly%20perturbed%20by%20violence%20taking%20place.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%205%20in%20the%20morning%20of%20August%209%2C%20a%20day%20after%20the%20AICC%20ratified%20the%20Quit%20India%20resolution%2C%20Gandhi%2C%20Nehru%2C%20Patel%2C%20Azad%20and%20all%20top%20Congress%20leaders%20were%20arrested.%20Though%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20had%20been%20imprisoned%20at%20Aga%20Khan%20Palace%20at%20Poona%2C%20was%20released%20earlier%20in%20May%201944%20on%20grounds%20of%20health%2C%20Nehru%20was%20in%20prison%20at%20Ahmednagar%20Fort%20for%2034%20months%2C%20his%20longest%20ever%2C%20from%20August%201942%20to%20June%201945.%20The%20wholesale%20arrest%20of%20the%20leaders%20touched%20off%20a%20spontaneous%20popular%20revolt%20throughout%20India.%20For%20a%20week%20all%20business%20was%20paralysed%20in%20Bombay%2C%20Ahmedabad%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Bangalore%2C%20Calcutta%20and%20many%20other%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authorities%20let%20loose%20cruel%20repression.%20In%20Delhi%2C%20the%20police%20fired%20on%2047%20separate%20occasions%20on%20August%2011%20and%2012.%20In%20UP%20there%20were%2029%20firings%20between%20August%209%20and%2021%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20death%20of%2076%20persons%20and%20severe%20injury%20to%20114.%20In%20the%20Central%20Provinces%20the%20police%20killed%2064%2C%20wounded%20102%20and%20arrested%2011%2C088%20in%20the%20first%20three%20weeks.%20In%20Mysore%20State%20about%20600%20persons%20were%20killed%20by%20police%20firing%20during%20the%20first%20few%20days%20of%20the%20movement.%20In%20Patiala%2C%20eight%20students%20were%20killed%20while%20trying%20to%20hoist%20the%20national%20flag%20over%20a%20public%20building.%20Over%20100%20were%20shot%20in%20a%20Mysore%20procession.%20In%20Calcutta%20there%20were%20numerous%20firings%2C%20resulting%20in%20many%20deaths.%20The%20same%20was%20the%20case%20in%20all%20big%20cities.%20In%20Midnapore%20(Bengal)%20and%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20parallel%20governments%20were%20set%20up%20which%20functioned%20effectively%20for%20a%20short%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20casualties%20from%20August%209%20to%20November%2030%2C%201942%20were%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Secretary%20of%20State%20for%20India%2C%201%2C008%20killed%2C%20and%203%2C275%20seriously%20injured.%20The%20popular%20estimate%20was%20however%20very%20much%20higher.%20The%20number%20of%20people%20imprisoned%20was%20over%20100%2C000.%20The%20movement%20had%20taken%20a%20turn%20not%20contemplated%20by%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20Congress%20leaders.%20Infuriated%20by%20the%20wholesale%20arrest%20of%20their%20leaders%20and%20the%20cruel%20repression%20let%20loose%20by%20the%20authorities%2C%20people%20in%20several%20places%20destroyed%20public%20property%20like%20bridges%2C%20police%20stations%2C%20etc.%2C%20and%20removed%20even%20rail%20tracks%2C%20cut%20off%20telegraph%20wires%20and%20vented%20their%20anger%20in%20various%20other%20acts%20of%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcharya%20Kriplani%20(who%20was%20INC%20president%20in%201946-47)%20writes%20in%20his%20biography%20of%20Gandhi%3A%20%E2%80%9CHad%20the%20people%20had%20the%20guidance%20of%20the%20leaders%2C%20such%20wanton%20destruction%20would%20not%20have%20taken%20place.%20Even%20if%20Gandhiji%20alone%20were%20out%2C%20he%20would%20have%20undertaken%20a%20fast%20if%20nothing%20else%20had%20prevailed.%20It%20would%20have%20cooled%20down%20people%E2%80%99s%20ardour%20for%20destruction%20and%20the%20movement%20would%20have%20gone%20on%20generally%20on%20right%20lines.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Kriplani%20held%20the%20firm%20view%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20my%20opinion%20that%20India%20could%20not%20have%20achieved%20its%20independence%2C%20but%20for%20the%20accession%20of%20strength%20which%20the%20nation%20received%20by%20the%20successive%20struggles%20started%20by%20Gandhiji.%20A%20nation%20which%20could%20throw%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%20Empire%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20armies%20of%20all%20the%20Allies%20were%20on%20Indian%20soil%20could%20no%20more%20be%20held%20in%20thralldom.%E2%80%9D%20Even%20if%20one%20is%20wiser%20by%20hindsight%2C%20the%20Acharya%E2%80%99s%20opinion%20is%20difficult%20to%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPraveen%20Davar%20is%20former%20secretary%2C%20AICC%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EFreedom%20Struggle%20%26amp%3B%20Beyond%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691489452000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F08%2FQuit-India-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fquit-india-the-last-nail-in-the-coffin-of-the-british-empire%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20movement%20took%20a%20turn%20not%20contemplated%20by%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20Congress%20leaders.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fquit-india-the-last-nail-in-the-coffin-of-the-british-empire%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Adani%20Ports%20Q1FY24%20results%3A%20Consolidated%20net%20profit%20up%2080%25%20to%20Rs%202%2C119%20cr%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691489298000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2021-03%2F03%2Ffull%2F1614784663-3212.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fadani-ports-q1fy24-results-consolidated-net-profit-up-80-to-rs-2-119-cr-123080800456_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20net%20profit%20was%2085.7%20per%20cent%20higher%20as%20compared%20to%20Rs%201%2C140.97%20crore%20in%20the%20quarter%20that%20ended%20on%20March%2031%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fadani-ports-q1fy24-results-consolidated-net-profit-up-80-to-rs-2-119-cr-123080800456_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fadani-ports-q1fy24-results-consolidated-net-profit-up-80-to-rs-2-119-cr-123080800456_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fadani-ports-q1fy24-results-consolidated-net-profit-up-80-to-rs-2-119-cr-123080800456_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Carlyle%20to%20acquire%20minority%20stake%20in%20Quest%20Global%3B%20Bain%2C%20Advent%20to%20exit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691488836000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-05%2F02%2Ffull%2F1683013227-7789.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcarlyle-to-acquire-minority-stake-in-quest-global-bain-advent-to-exit-123080800442_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ajit%20Prabhu%2C%20chairman%20and%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20Quest%20Global%2C%20will%20acquire%20an%20additional%20stake%20in%20the%20company%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcarlyle-to-acquire-minority-stake-in-quest-global-bain-advent-to-exit-123080800442_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcarlyle-to-acquire-minority-stake-in-quest-global-bain-advent-to-exit-123080800442_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcarlyle-to-acquire-minority-stake-in-quest-global-bain-advent-to-exit-123080800442_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Banks%20Wrote%20off%20Rs%2014.56%20Lakh%20Crore%20Since%202014-15%3A%20Govt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F01%2F24173925%2Fcurrency_pti.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Banks%20have%20written%20off%20bad%20loans%20worth%20Rs%2014.56%20lakh%20crore%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20financial%20years%20starting%202014-15%2C%20parliament%20was%20informed%20on%20Monday%2C%20August%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20PTI%2C%20out%20of%20the%20total%20Rs%2014%2C56%2C226%20crore%2C%20written%20off%20loans%20of%20large%20industries%20and%20services%20stood%20at%20Rs%207%2C40%2C968%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScheduled%20Commercial%20Banks%20have%20recovered%20an%20aggregate%20amount%20of%20Rs%202%2C04%2C668%20crore%20in%20written-off%20loans%2C%20including%20corporate%20loans%2C%20since%20April%202014%20and%20up%20to%20March%2C%202023%2C%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Finance%20Bhagwat%20Karad%20said%20in%20a%20written%20reply%20to%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20another%20reply%20by%20the%20minister%2C%20the%20net%20of%20recovery%20in%20written-off%20loans%20during%20the%20financial%20year%20(net%20write-off)%20in%20public%20sector%20banks%20(PSBs)%20was%20Rs%201.18%20lakh%20crore%20in%20the%20FY18%2C%20which%20declined%20to%20Rs%200.91%20lakh%20crore%20in%20FY22%20and%20to%20Rs%200.84%20lakh%20crore%20(RBI%20provisional%20data)%20in%20FY23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20write-off%20loans%20by%20private%20sector%20banks%20stood%20at%20Rs%2073%2C803%20crore%20(RBI%20provisional%20data)%20in%20FY23%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20write-off%20as%20percentage%20of%20opening%20gross%20loans%20and%20advances%20in%20private%20sector%20banks%20was%201.25%25%20and%201.57%25%20in%20FY18%20and%20FY23%2C%20respectively.%20It%20was%202%25%20and%201.12%25%20for%20PSBs%20during%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%2C%20banks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbad-loans-npas-written-off-rbi%5C%22%3Ewrote%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20non-performing%20assets%20(NPAs)%2C%20or%20bad%20loans%2C%20worth%20over%20Rs%202.09%20lakh%20crore%20(around%20%24%2025.50%20billion)%20during%20the%20year%20ended%20March%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20the%20total%20loan%20write-offs%20by%20the%20banking%20sector%20stood%20at%20Rs%2010.57%20lakh%20crore%2C%20the%20Indian%20Express%20reported%2C%20citing%20an%20RTI%20response%20from%20the%20central%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20loan%20is%20classified%20as%20an%20NPA%20when%20the%20repayment%20of%20the%20principal%20amount%20or%20the%20interest%20remains%20outstanding%20for%20a%20period%20of%2090%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20measures%20taken%20to%20bring%20down%20bad%20loans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20support%20asset%20growth%2C%20the%20board%20of%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20in%20its%20meeting%20held%20on%20June%209%20had%20approved%20raising%20capital%20through%20bonds%2C%20including%20Rs%2020%2C000%20crore%20via%20Basel%20III%20compliant%20AT-1%20bonds%2C%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore%20via%20Tier-2%20bonds%2C%20and%20Rs%2020%2C000%20crore%20via%20infrastructure%20bonds%20during%20FY24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Karad%2C%20banks%20are%20exempted%20from%20maintaining%20cash%20reserve%20ratio%20and%20statutory%20liquidity%20ratio%20on%20long-term%20bonds%20for%20lending%20to%20the%20infrastructure%20sector.%20The%20raising%20of%20long-term%20infrastructure%20bonds%20helps%20the%20bank%20in%20better%20asset%20liability%20management%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20steps%20to%20bring%20down%20NPAs%2C%20the%20minister%20said%20that%20the%20Securitisation%20and%20Reconstruction%20of%20Financial%20Assets%20and%20Enforcement%20of%20Security%20Interest%20Act%2C%202002%2C%20has%20been%20amended%20to%20make%20it%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20monetary%20limit%20for%20filing%20cases%20in%20debt%20recovery%20tribunals%20(DRTs)%20was%20increased%20from%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20to%20Rs%2020%20lakh.%20This%20enables%20the%20DRTs%20to%20focus%20on%20high-value%20cases%2C%20resulting%20in%20higher%20recovery%20for%20the%20banks%20and%20financial%20institutions%2C%20the%20minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%20that%20the%20National%20Asset%20Reconstruction%20Company%20Limited%20(NARCL)%20has%20been%20set%20up%20as%20an%20asset%20reconstruction%20company%20with%20an%20aim%20to%20resolve%20stressed%20assets%20above%20Rs%20500%20crore%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENARCL%20is%20bad%20bank%2C%20which%20buys%20NPAs%2C%20or%20bad%20loans%2C%20from%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENARCL%20acquired%20three%20borrower%20entities%2C%20including%20Jaypee%20Infratech%2C%20with%20an%20aggregate%20debt%20exposure%20of%20Rs%2021%2C349%20crore%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%20FY23%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Findustry%2Fnarcl-acquires-rs-21349-cr-toxic-assets-far-cry-from-target%2F3185153%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20targets%20set%20for%20transfer%20of%20toxic%20assets%20to%20the%20NARCL.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202021%2C%20the%20NARCL%20got%20a%20licence%20from%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20start%20operations%2C%20and%20as%20per%20the%20initial%20target%2C%20it%20was%20to%20acquire%20a%20batch%20of%20toxic%20assets%20worth%20about%20Rs%2090%2C000%20crore%20by%20January%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691488831000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F01%2F24173925%2Fcurrency_pti.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbanks-wrote-off-rs-14-56-lakh-crore-since-2014-15-govt%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Out%20of%20the%20total%20Rs%2014%2C56%2C226%20crore%2C%20written%20off%20loans%20of%20large%20industries%20and%20services%2