hebetterindia.com%2F271536%2Fdesigners-use-renewable-solar-energy-rainwater-fashion%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Institute%20of%20Design%3C%2Fa%3E%20(NID)%2C%20Kirat%20started%20to%20work%20as%20an%20animation%20designer.%20%E2%80%9CI%20worked%20in%20the%20industry%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20for%20clients%20all%20over%20the%20country.%20I%20loved%20experimenting%20with%20design%20and%20various%20aspects%20of%20animation%2C%20but%20deep%20down%2C%20I%20always%20longed%20for%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%2032-year-old.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Kirat%20lived%20in%20various%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20he%20became%20more%20aware%20of%20the%20discrimination%20and%20lack%20of%20awareness%20concerning%20people%20from%20the%20Northeastern%20states.%20By%202020%2C%20when%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20Kirat%20had%20made%20up%20his%20mind%20to%20return%20home%20and%20start%20looking%20for%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20product%20that%20highlights%20our%20culture%20to%20the%20upcoming%20generations.%20I%20also%20wanted%20to%20open%20a%20whole%20new%20world%20for%20people%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20Bodo%20culture.%20What%20could%20be%20a%20better%20way%20of%20introducing%20kids%20and%20people%20to%20my%20culture%20than%20with%20soft%20toys%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20he%20started%20Zankla%20Studio%20in%202021%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20showcasing%20the%20rich%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F135223%2Fassam-bodoland-lakme-women-weavers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20culture%20of%20the%20Bodo%20Tribe%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20studio%20creates%20handmade%20plastic-free%20soft%20toys%20that%20narrate%20stories%20deeply%20connected%20to%20the%20local%20culture%20and%20traditions%20of%20the%20Bodo%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ERepresenting%20people%20from%20the%20Bodo%20communi